UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Cyrus VANCE, Defendant-Appellant. No. 13-13079

Non-Argument Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. March 6, 2014. Robert Benjamin Cornell, Richard O.I. Brown, Phillip Drew Dirosa, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Fort Lauderdale, FL, Wifre-do A. Ferre, Kathleen Mary Salyer, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Miami, FL, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Cyrus Vance, Lexington, KY, pro se. PER CURIAM:

The court has reviewed the record and the briefs of the parties, and has reviewed the findings and conclusion s of the district court. We find no error and the judgment of the district court is

AFFIRMED.
